type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"a266c503-042a-43d0-b46e-cbd629b86c30\",\"toolUseID\":\"a266c503-042a-43d0-b46e-cbd629b86c30\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T00:15:33.510Z\",\"uuid\":\"c4030b88-02f4-4b04-87cf-d38881304926\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c4030b88-02f4-4b04-87cf-d38881304926\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"f6361a7e-c7e7-4190-ac8c-97fe80954831\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"recursive-giggling-reef\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Support Kiro IDE transcript format for session metadata\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nAfter fixing the stop hook exit code (returning nil for empty repos), the hooks run successfully in the Kiro IDE. However, `full.jsonl`, `prompt.txt`, and `summary.txt` are all empty because the transcript is just a `{}` placeholder.\\n\\n**Root cause**: `ensureCachedTranscript()` queries `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (the kiro-cli database), but the **Kiro IDE stores conversations in a completely different location and format**:\\n\\n- **Location**: `~/Library/Application Support/Kiro/User/globalStorage/kiro.kiroagent/workspace-sessions/<base64-encoded-cwd>/<session-uuid>.json`\\n- **Index**: `sessions.json` in the same directory lists all sessions with `sessionId`, `title`, `dateCreated`, `workspaceDirectory`\\n- **Format**: Sequential `{role, content}` messages (like Anthropic API format), NOT the paired `{user, assistant}` entries the kiro-cli uses\\n\\n### Format comparison\\n\\n**kiro-cli (SQLite, current parser)**:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"history\\\": [\\n    { \\\"user\\\": { \\\"content\\\": {\\\"Prompt\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\"...\\\"}} }, \\\"assistant\\\": {\\\"Response\\\": {\\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}} }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Kiro IDE (JSON files, what we need to support)**:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"history\\\": [\\n    { \\\"message\\\": { \\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}] } },\\n    { \\\"message\\\": { \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"On it.\\\" }, \\\"promptLogs\\\": [...] }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nTwo changes needed: (1) find the transcript from the IDE storage, (2) parse the IDE format.\\n\\n### 1. IDE transcript discovery (`kiro.go`)\\n\\nAdd `ensureIDETranscript()` that:\\n1. Computes `ideWorkspaceSessionsDir()` → `~/Library/Application Support/Kiro/User/globalStorage/kiro.kiroagent/workspace-sessions/<base64(cwd)>/`\\n2. Reads `sessions.json` index, sorts by `dateCreated` descending to find most recent session\\n3. Reads the session JSON file and copies it to `.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json`\\n\\nCall this from `parseStop()` — after `ensureCachedTranscript()` fails and before `createPlaceholderTranscript()`:\\n\\n```go\\n// lifecycle.go parseStop(), lines 154-163\\nsessionRef, _ := k.ensureCachedTranscript(ctx, cwd, sessionID)\\nif sessionRef == \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionRef, _ = k.ensureIDETranscript(ctx, cwd, sessionID)  // NEW\\n}\\nif sessionRef == \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionRef = k.createPlaceholderTranscript(ctx, cwd, sessionID)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Dual-format transcript parsing (`transcript.go`)\\n\\nUpdate `parseTranscript()` to detect the format and normalize both into `kiroTranscript`:\\n\\n- **Detection**: If the raw JSON has `history[0].message.role`, it's IDE format. If it has `history[0].user`, it's CLI format.\\n- **Conversion**: Convert IDE sequential messages into paired `kiroHistoryEntry` entries so all downstream code (ExtractPrompts, ExtractSummary, ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset) works unchanged.\\n\\nAdd IDE-specific types to `types.go`:\\n```go\\ntype kiroIDEHistoryEntry struct {\\n    Message struct {\\n        Role    string          `json:\\\"role\\\"`\\n        Content json.RawMessage `json:\\\"content\\\"`\\n    } `json:\\\"message\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\nUpdate `parseTranscript()`:\\n```go\\nfunc parseTranscript(data []byte) (*kiroTranscript, error) {\\n    // Try CLI format first\\n    var t kiroTranscript\\n    if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &t); err != nil { ... }\\n    if len(t.History) > 0 { return &t, nil }\\n\\n    // Try IDE format\\n    var ide kiroIDETranscript\\n    if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &ide); err != nil { ... }\\n    if len(ide.History) > 0 { return convertIDETranscript(ide), nil }\\n\\n    return &kiroTranscript{}, nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nUpdate extraction functions to handle IDE content format:\\n- `extractUserPrompt()`: Also handle `[{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}]` array format (in addition to `{\\\"Prompt\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\"...\\\"}}`)\\n- `extractLastAssistantResponse()`: Also handle plain string content (in addition to `{\\\"Response\\\": {...}}`)\\n\\n### 3. IDE workspace path helper (`kiro.go`)\\n\\n```go\\nfunc ideWorkspaceSessionsDir(cwd string) (string, error) {\\n    home, err := os.UserHomeDir()\\n    // macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Kiro/User/globalStorage/kiro.kiroagent/workspace-sessions/<base64(cwd)>/\\n    // linux: TBD (Kiro IDE isn't on Linux yet, but use XDG if needed)\\n    encoded := base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString([]byte(cwd))\\n    return filepath.Join(home, \\\"Library\\\", \\\"Application Support\\\", \\\"Kiro\\\", \\\"User\\\", \\\"globalStorage\\\", \\\"kiro.kiroagent\\\", \\\"workspace-sessions\\\", encoded), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: The base64 encoding uses standard encoding (not URL-safe) with no padding trimming — verified by decoding the actual directory name `REDACTED`.\\n\\n## Files to modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` | Add IDE transcript types (`kiroIDETranscript`, `kiroIDEHistoryEntry`) |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/transcript.go` | Update `parseTranscript()` for dual-format detection; update `extractUserPrompt()` and `extractLastAssistantResponse()` to handle IDE content formats |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/kiro.go` | Add `ensureIDETranscript()`, `ideWorkspaceSessionsDir()`, IDE sessions.json types |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` | Call `ensureIDETranscript()` in `parseStop()` fallback chain |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/transcript_test.go` | Add tests for IDE format parsing, prompt extraction, summary extraction |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThen test in the Kiro IDE with the test repo at `/Users/alisha/Projects/test-repos/kiro-ide`:\\n1. Start a new Kiro session with a prompt like \\\"create hello world in python\\\"\\n2. After it completes, check that `full.jsonl` has real transcript content (not `{}`)\\n3. Check that `prompt.txt` contains the user prompt\\n4. Check that `summary.txt` contains the assistant response\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/75dc86c1-99d8-40a8-ba1e-018fbe0b4e9c.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"1cbd0cf6-d03c-4f80-9946-3d3106954882\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T00:15:33.131Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: Support Kiro IDE transcript format for session metadata\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nAfter fixing the stop hook exit code (returning nil for empty repos), the hooks run successfully in the Kiro IDE. However, `full.jsonl`, `prompt.txt`, and `summary.txt` are all empty because the transcript is just a `{}` placeholder.\\n\\n**Root cause**: `ensureCachedTranscript()` queries `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (the kiro-cli database), but the **Kiro IDE stores conversations in a completely different 